                                                                                                NIST SP 800-175B REV. 1                          GUIDELINE FOR USING CRYPTO STANDARDS IN THE
                                                                                                                                                              FED. GOV'T.: CRYPTO MECHANISMS


                                                                                                                            1. Source authentication,
                                                                                                                            2. Data integrity, and
                                                                                                                            3. Support for signer non-repudiation.

                                                                                                 Digital Signature        A public-key algorithm that is used for the generation and
                                                                                                 Algorithm (DSA)          verification of digital signatures.

                                                                                                 Domain parameters        The parameters used with a cryptographic algorithm that are
                                                                                                                          common to a domain of users.

                                                                                                 Elliptic Curve Digital   A digital signature algorithm that is an analog of DSA using
This publication is available free of charge from: https://doi.org/10.6028/NIST.SP.800-175Br1




                                                                                                 Signature Algorithm      elliptic curves.
                                                                                                 (ECDSA)

                                                                                                 Encryption               The process of changing plaintext into ciphertext using a
                                                                                                                          cryptographic algorithm for the purpose of security or privacy.

                                                                                                 Entity                   An individual (person), organization, device, or process.

                                                                                                 Ephemeral key pair       A short-term key pair used with a public-key (asymmetric-key)
                                                                                                                          algorithm that is generated when needed; the public key of an
                                                                                                                          ephemeral key pair is not provided in a public key certificate,
                                                                                                                          unlike static public keys which are often included in a certificate.

                                                                                                 Function                 Used interchangeably with algorithm in this document.

                                                                                                 Hash function            See cryptographic hash function.

                                                                                                 Hash value               The result of applying a hash function to information; also called
                                                                                                                          a message digest.

                                                                                                 Identity                 The process of providing assurance about the identity of an
                                                                                                 authentication           entity interacting with a system; also see Source authentication.

                                                                                                 Initialization Vector    A vector used in defining the starting point of a cryptographic
                                                                                                 (IV)                     process.

                                                                                                 Integrity                The property that data has not been modified or deleted in an
                                                                                                                          unauthorized and undetected manner.

                                                                                                 Integrity                The process of determining the integrity of the data; also called
                                                                                                 authentication           data integrity authentication.
                                                                                                 (integrity verification)

                                                                                                 Interoperability         The ability of one entity to communicate with another entity.

                                                                                                 Key                      See cryptographic key.




